 <!--
   Tile ID Legend:
   Ground Layer:   1 = stone floor (passable), 2 = acid corroded floor (dangerous)
   Walls Layer:   0 = solid wall (impassable), 3 = operating table / stone pillar (blocks movement + sight)
   Mechanics Layer: 4 = poison trap, 5 = diary desk, 6 = loot chest, 7 = heavy oak door (exit)

   Map Layout (25x25):
   - Area A (y=17-24): Abandoned Foyer - player spawn point (safe buffer zone)
   - Area B (x=1-8, y=9-16): Specimen Storage Corridor - acid floor + poison traps, winding north
   - Area C (x=19-24, y=9-15): Secret Study - diary desk (int check) + loot chest
   - Area D (y=1-8): Main Operating Room - Gribbo, tables/pillars for cover, north exit door

   Coordinate system: x=0..24 (left to right), y=0..24 (top to bottom)
 -->

